attachments.title: The Post PSD Era doesn’t want to kill designers.
attachments.text: In fact, it needs them more than ever.
attachments.fallback: Medium: The Post PSD Era doesn’t want to kill designers.

text: More on the idea of designing systems and styles instead of static comps.
That was a really good read, I enjoyed it. Thanks for sharing gaston.

Awesome,  <@U026E0ZNR>. There's been a lot of posts around this idea in the last year. Not sure if everything is applicable to what we do and the type of clients we work with but it's interesting to see how the industry is moving forward.
you know whats funny - I've been reading this same article since about 2002. It's interesting to me that this idea both doesn't ever die but also never really takes hold
Ha <@U0260V4K1>. I guess the industry always finds ways to complain about how we do things :wink:
yeah - i mean, I don't think it's a bad thing. I take it more as a representation that there's something not quiet right in the way we typically work, and people are still trying to figure it out
for my part, my feeling is that problem is more cultural than it is technologically
but since few of us are in position to change the culture, we're forced to address the technique
